 local-cache coverage without services, but its transaction APIs rely on provided JTA and a real transaction manager; existing coverage also needs update checks disabled to avoid network/background behavior.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.transaction:jta:1.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"ehcache-core declares JTA as provided and exposes/uses javax.transaction types in transaction APIs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.codehaus.btm:btm:2.1.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Ehcache documentation describes JTA transactions under an application-server or third-party transaction manager such as Bitronix; DefaultTransactionManagerLookup coverage needs a concrete manager.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.geronimo.specs:geronimo-jms_1.1_spec:1.1.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Bitronix references javax.jms classes through optional JMS support, so the JMS API prevents classpath/native-image missing-type issues when Bitronix is analyzed.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set net.sf.ehcache.skipUpdateCheck=true in tests, or ensure all CacheManager/configuration creation uses updateCheck(false)/updateCheck=\\\"false\\\". Use temporary diskStore paths for disk persistence tests. If using Bitronix, point bitronix.tm.configuration at a temporary properties file with bitronix.tm.disableJmx=true and bitronix.tm.journal=null, then shut down the transaction manager and clear the property after each test.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Do not require a Docker service for normal ehcache-core coverage; avoid Terracotta clustered-cache scenarios unless explicitly adding a Terracotta server setup.\",\n    \"Hibernate and servlet integration classes are present but depend on provided containers/APIs; broad tests that load those integrations may require additional setup and are not necessary for core coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0790f86d7b3a0b23016a42f2c7f2888195a13b0ed7235c0ae7\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1895, "output": 978, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37689, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782772415704, "responseId": "resp_0790f86d7b3a0b23016a42f2c04b7081958a82bbbbe9559575"}, "toolResults": []}
